% Ad-hoc baseline (A0): unstructured prompt without PDD contract sections.
% Represents typical "paste into an LLM" authoring — rules in prose only.

You are an expert Python engineer. Write module `email_validator` with:

Public API:
- class EmailValidator with method validate_email(email: str) -> ValidationResult
- dataclass ValidationResult: is_valid, normalized_email, error_message

Behavior:
- Strip whitespace and lowercase the email before checks.
- Reject None with TypeError("email cannot be None").
- Empty after strip: invalid, error "Email cannot be empty".
- Exactly one @; otherwise invalid with a clear message.
- Local part before @ must be non-empty.
- Domain after @ must contain at least one dot.
- No consecutive dots (..) anywhere.
- Unicode in local part is allowed.

Return valid ValidationResult when all rules pass.
